---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - The Realm of Patterns" description="How we collect, use, and protect your data at The Realm of Patterns.">
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="page-container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="effective-date">Effective Date: February 4, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <section>
          <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            The Realm of Patterns ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy.
            This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information
            when you use our website and services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Privacy-First Architecture</h2>
          <p>
            We use a <strong>privacy by design</strong> approach with advanced cryptographic techniques
            to protect your data. Our system is designed so that <strong>even we cannot read your personal information</strong>.
          </p>

          <h3>2.1 Local-First Storage</h3>
          <p>
            By default, your birth data stays on your device only. It is stored in your browser's
            local storage and never transmitted to our servers unless you explicitly enable sync.
          </p>

          <h3>2.2 Encryption</h3>
          <p>
            If you choose to sync your data, it is encrypted using <strong>AES-256-GCM</strong> encryption
            before leaving your device. The encryption key is derived from your device ID using PBKDF2
            with 100,000 iterations. This means only your device can decrypt your data.
          </p>

          <h3>2.3 Pseudonymization</h3>
          <p>
            Your identity is represented by a SHA-256 hash of your device ID plus a server secret.
            This hash cannot be reversed to identify you. We separate your encrypted identity from
            your astrological data - so we can analyze patterns without knowing who you are.
          </p>

          <h3>2.4 Data Separation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Encrypted Vault:</strong> Your birth data (encrypted, we cannot read it)</li>
            <li><strong>Astrology Data:</strong> Check-ins, vectors, stages (contains no personal information)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3>3.1 Information You Provide</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Birth Data:</strong> Date, time, and location of birth - <em>stored on your device only, encrypted if synced</em></li>
            <li><strong>Check-in Responses:</strong> Your answers to the daily check-in - <em>linked only by anonymous hash</em></li>
            <li><strong>Email Address:</strong> Only if you subscribe - <em>encrypted in our vault</em></li>
            <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Processed by Stripe; we never see or store card numbers</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Device ID:</strong> A random UUID generated on your device, used for sync</li>
            <li><strong>Country Code:</strong> For language preferences (not stored with your profile)</li>
            <li><strong>Aggregated Analytics:</strong> Anonymous usage patterns (no individual tracking)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.3 What We DON'T Collect</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Your name (unless you tell us)</li>
            <li>Your exact location or GPS coordinates</li>
            <li>Your IP address (beyond the current request)</li>
            <li>Your browsing history</li>
            <li>Data from other apps or websites</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Calculate your energy profile</li>
            <li>Provide personalized readings and recommendations</li>
            <li>Track your pattern over time (history feature)</li>
            <li>Process payments and manage subscriptions</li>
            <li>Send service-related communications</li>
            <li>Improve our services through aggregated analytics</li>
            <li>Prevent fraud and ensure security</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
          <p>We do not sell your personal data. We share information only in these limited circumstances:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Stripe (payments), Cloudflare (hosting), necessary third parties</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law or to protect rights</li>
            <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with mergers or acquisitions</li>
            <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> When you explicitly agree to sharing</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Circle (Team) Features</h2>
          <p>
            If you join a Circle, certain pattern data may be visible to other Circle members as part
            of the shared dashboard feature. You can control what is shared through your privacy settings.
            Circle facilitators can see aggregated coherence metrics but not individual check-in responses
            unless you choose to share them.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Data Storage and Security</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Encryption at Rest:</strong> All personal data encrypted with AES-256-GCM</li>
            <li><strong>Encryption in Transit:</strong> HTTPS for all data transmission</li>
            <li><strong>Zero-Knowledge:</strong> Your birth data is encrypted with a key only your device has</li>
            <li><strong>Pseudonymization:</strong> Your identity is a one-way hash we cannot reverse</li>
            <li><strong>Data Separation:</strong> Personal info separated from analytics data</li>
            <li><strong>Cloudflare Infrastructure:</strong> Enterprise-grade security and global distribution</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain your data as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services.
            After account deletion, we retain data for up to 30 days for backup purposes, then permanently delete it.
            Aggregated, anonymized data may be retained indefinitely for research and improvement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
          <p>We honor GDPR rights for <strong>all users worldwide</strong>, not just EU residents:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Right to Access (Art. 15):</strong> View all data we have about you</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Portability (Art. 20):</strong> Export your data in JSON format</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Rectification (Art. 16):</strong> Update your birth data anytime</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Erasure (Art. 17):</strong> Permanently delete all your data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Opt out of any processing</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To exercise these rights, visit <a href="/settings">Settings</a> or email
            <a href="mailto:privacy@therealmofpatterns.com">privacy@therealmofpatterns.com</a>.
            We respond within 30 days (usually much faster).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
          <p>We use:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> For authentication and security</li>
            <li><strong>Local storage:</strong> For preferences, mode selection, and offline functionality</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> To understand usage patterns (can be disabled)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are not intended for users under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children.
            If we learn we have collected data from a child under 13, we will delete it promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. International Users</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are hosted globally via Cloudflare. By using our services, you consent to
            the transfer of your data to servers that may be located outside your country of residence.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of material changes
            via email or prominent notice on our website. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            For privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at:
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@therealmofpatterns.com
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    --gold: #d4a854;
    --dark: #0a0908;
    --dark-surface: #141210;
    --text: #f0e8d8;
    --text-muted: rgba(240, 232, 216, 0.6);

    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    background: var(--dark);
    color: var(--text);
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem;
  }

  .page-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212, 168, 84, 0.2);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
  }

  .effective-date {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content li strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
